# Rule adherence
Before editing any file:
- Find the matching entries in the index below and read those rules, unless they are already in your context
- Once per file type per session is enough — no need to re-read rules already loaded

## Rule index
Match on the code being produced, not just the file extension — snippets inside Markdown, plan files, and chat responses count:
- Any JavaScript or TypeScript code → `./formatting/js-ts.mdc`
- Markdown (`.md`, `.mdc`) → `./formatting/md.mdc`
- Shell scripts or commands (sh, bash, zsh) → `./formatting/sh.mdc`
- YAML → `./formatting/yml.mdc`
- Plan files and prompt logs (`.cursor/plans/**/*.md`) → `./plans.mdc`

When adding, removing, or re-scoping rules in the cursor-config repository, update this index there — not in a synced copy.

After editing:
- Re-read your diff and verify it adheres to every applicable rule; fix violations, only then perform your tests
